==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sirrah
<hw>Sir"rah</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably from Icel.
<ets>s⟦imac⟧ra</ets>, fr. F. <ets>sire</ets>. See <er>Sir</er>.]</ety>
<def>A term of address implying inferiority and used in anger, contempt,
reproach, or disrespectful familiarity, addressed to a man or boy, but
sometimes to a woman. In sililoquies often preceded by <xex>ah</xex>.
Not used in the plural.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Ah, <xex>sirrah</xex>
mistress.⟦rdquo⟧ <-- archaic --> <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Go, <qex>sirrah</qex>, to my cell.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sirt</ent>⟦br⟧
